  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: Missiles<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Research Preference: Power and Shields<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Visareen</span> (used plura=
l and
  singular) are a generally peaceful race, however they take extreme pride =
in
  the outward show of strength. They will make great efforts to have a very
  large military, and their entire culture is based around military shows,
  competitions and displays. Most <span class=3DSpellE>Visareens</span> wil=
l grow
  up with the desire to enter and serve in their military forces in some wa=
y.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Visareen's</span> leader, is
  considered by many <span class=3DSpellE>Visareen</span> to be a god, and =
to the
  rest they believe he is directly related or gifted by a spiritual being.<=
o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Visareen</span> make a some=
what
  cold <span class=3DSpellE>neighbour</span> to other Empires, appearing
  threatening with their overt displays of strength but in <span class=3DGr=
amE>reality</span>
  they will rarely make any actions to invoke actual conflict.<o:p></o:p></=
p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Visareen</span> live in lar=
ge
  spread-out communities all centered around their own temples built to hear
  the frequent preaching of their leader.</p>
